      "content": "When originalism is used to overturn modern social understandings, it is precisely because the originalists believe those understandings represent a departure from the founders' intent. The perceived \"political outcome\" is, in the view of its supporters, the preservation of the original constitutional structure against modern judicial overreach. This application is a direct reflection of the theory's commitment to textual fidelity over contemporary social engineering.",
      "source": "target",
